### Rekap Remote API Tests
### Base URL: http://localhost:3000/api/rekap-remote

### 1. Get Rekap Data
GET http://localhost:3000/api/rekap-remote/data
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 2. Get Rekap Data with filters
GET http://localhost:3000/api/rekap-remote/data?kdtk=0001&module_name=rekon_wt_harian&status=success
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 3. Get Summary Statistics
GET http://localhost:3000/api/rekap-remote/summary
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Get Summary with filters
GET http://localhost:3000/api/rekap-remote/summary?module_name=rekon_wt_harian
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 5. Get Log Count (in memory)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/rekap-remote/logs/count
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 6. Save Logs Manually (force save current in-memory logs)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/rekap-remote/logs/save
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

### 7. Clear Logs (from memory)
DELETE http://localhost:3000/api/rekap-remote/logs/clear
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 8. Test Manual Log Creation (for testing purposes)
### Note: This would require adding test data manually via service
### Example of how logs are created during rekon_wt_harian process:
### RekapRemoteService.logSuccess('0001', 'rekon_wt_harian', 'Test success message')
### RekapRemoteService.logError('0002', 'rekon_wt_harian', 'Test error message')
### RekapRemoteService.logTimeout('0003', 'rekon_wt_harian', 'Test timeout message')
### RekapRemoteService.logFailure('0004', 'rekon_wt_harian', 'Test failure message')

### 9. Get Rekap Data for specific store
GET http://localhost:3000/api/rekap-remote/data?kdtk=0001
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 10. Get Rekap Data for specific module
GET http://localhost:3000/api/rekap-remote/data?module_name=rekon_wt_harian
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 11. Get Recent Rekap Data (last 24 hours)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/rekap-remote/data?hours=24
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 12. Get Summary by Status
GET http://localhost:3000/api/rekap-remote/summary?status=success
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 13. Get Summary by Status (error)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/rekap-remote/summary?status=error
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 14. Get Summary by Status (timeout)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/rekap-remote/summary?status=timeout
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 15. Get Summary by Status (failure)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/rekap-remote/summary?status=failure
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### Notes:
### - Replace YOUR_TOKEN_HERE with actual JWT token
### - Server should be running on http://localhost:3000
### - All endpoints require authentication
### - Data will be populated after running rekon_wt_harian process
### - Use the summary endpoint to get overview of store connection status
### - Use the data endpoint to get detailed logs for specific stores or modules